0 Comments
6 Days Ago





“First, there is Hon. Sanusi Rikiji, the in-law of Dahiru Mangal. Former Governor Senator Sani Yerima is currently asked to lead his lobbying. “Then there is the current Commissioner for Commerce, Mr Yazeed Fulani, who is also lobbying for the position. He is known to have a good connection with Senator Yerima and Mr Abba Sarki – the Personal Assistant on Domestic Affairs to President Buhari. “The third person is competing for the position is the current Senator of Zamfara Central, Senator Hassaan Nasiha. Insiders see him as a wild card that can balance the equation. It is rumoured that Senator Yerima will accept him as the Deputy Governor while Hon. Rikiji replaces him as the Senator for Zamfara Central zone. “The fourth contender is Mr Sufyan Bashir Yuguda, the current Commissioner for Finance. He is also the son of the former Nigerian Diplomat to UAE and former Minister of State Finance, Bashir Yuguda. It is alleged that Mr Yuguda has started distributing money to the Zamfara State Members of the House of Assembly as he begins to make a case for himself. “The fifth contender is Mr Jamilu Mohammed Dahiru Abubakar. He is the son of former IG police MD Abubakar and the son-in-law to (Aliko) Dangote (Africa’s richest man). We are yet to understand whether Yerima is working on his own or with Governor Matawalle. But it is clear that all eyes are on the governor, but it seems lobbying goes through Senator Yerima.”